frameDefinitions: This Frame is concerned with evaluating an Evaluee as being suitable for a Purpose or a User, presupposing some choice that is being made about which Evaluee to use for the Purpose or User.
An Entity aids in the successful completion of a Purpose.
An Agent is performing the portion of an Activity in which there is dynamic stability. '' 'Not noticing the hoards of people rushing by the window, Manny continued eating his lunch.'
A Supporter assists to strengthen the Supported by lending itself in material aid (or abstract assistance in the case of metaphorical uses).
An Agent manipulates an Instrument in order to achieve a Purpose.
An Agent has access to a finite amount of some Resource and uses it in some way to complete a Purpose.
frameExamples: (1) We need to build more houses <t>suitable</t> for local residents.
A box is an <t>ideal</t> storage device.
Not noticing the hoards of people rushing by the window, Manny <t>continued</t> eating his lunch.
The bottom of the wall is <t>supported</t> by the foundation.
For cold conditions, we recommend that you <t>use</t> a heat gun or a hair dryer to make the adhesive work better.
I <t>used</t> half of the bag of dirt to plant the roses.
listRoleDefinitions: This Frame Element marks constituents expressing the entity that is judged to be more or less suitable for some <fen>Purpose</fen> or <fen>User</fen>.
This Frame Element marks constituents that express the <fen>Purpose</fen> for which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged to be suitable or unsuitable.
This role marks expressions that indicate a <fen>User</fen> to whom
The item which is useful for some purpose.
The kind of task which is promoted by the use or presence of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
When the <fen>Entity</fen> is useful for a <fen>Purpose</fen>.

Duration denotes the length of <fen>Time</fen> from the beginning of a continuous situation (the one denoted by the target) to its end. In many cases, the continuous situation is a dynamic action which is ongoing, while in others it is simply an undifferentiated state.
This role identifies the name of the ongoing <fen>Activity</fen> in which an <fen>Agent</fen> engages.
The <fen>Agent</fen> engages in an ongoing <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when an ongoing <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the ongoing <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Supporter</fen> acts to benefit the <fex name='Supported'>Supported</fex> by providing additional strength or stability.
The <fen>Supported</fen> is given strength through the assistance of the <fen>Supporter</fen>.
This role identifies when the support occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the support occurs.
The Agent uses the Instrument to achieve their Purpose.
This role identifies the purpose for which an Agent uses the Instrument.
An entity directed by the <fen>Agent</fen> that serves to bring about the <fen>Purpose</fen> of the <fen>Agent</fen>.
An <fen>Instrument</fen> that has a function associated with it.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> uses the <fen>Instrument</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the Agent uses the Instrument.
The person who depletes a Resource to achieve some Goal
The exhaustible commodity that the <fen>Agent</fen> has access to.
What the <fen>Agent</fen> is attempting to achieve by using the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The amount of the <fen>Resource</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> uses to achieve the <fen>Purpose</fen>.
A more specific description of how the <fen>Purpose</fen> is achieved by spending the <fen>Resource</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Resource</fen> is used.
The physical location where the <fen>Resource</fen> is used.
